            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "mC@mwnXPLm",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "The loss function depends on {{c1::the data \\(\\mathcal D\\), the model \\(\\mathcal M\\), and the parameters \\( \\mathbf \\theta \\)::three things}}",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "hL6^Ss$Gog",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "Why is logistic regression called that, even though it's usually used for classification?<br>",
                "Beause it predicts a real number (probability), which then needs to be mapped to classes by a separate function.<br>"
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "zfZ$jzt.!,",
            "note_model_uuid": "c79b2657-64b6-11ea-a2b7-e550f5e55232",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "Ordinal regression is a type of regression used to predict an ordinal variable, i.e. a variable {{c1::on a scale where only the relative ordering of values is significant}}.",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "sXyNhmj8,6",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "Formally, in {{c2::multi-label}} classification you're predicting {{c1::an n-dimensional binary vector}}<br>",
                "where n is the number of labels<br>"
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "z-0z5`$02~",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::Structured (output) prediction}} refers to {{c1::techniques for predicting complex, structured objects, such as translation of a sentence or 3D structure of a protein.}}",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "r?S(p}VAzq",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "Most UL techniques are somehow based on {{c1::reconstruction}} error.",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "zX{lWw9N&U",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "Explore exploit tradeoff in reinforcement learning<div><br></div><div>Exploring: {{c1::taking novel actions to get feedback in order to find good actions to take}}</div><div>Exploiting: {{c1::taking actions already known to be relatively good}}</div>",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "DbG<kGbm~M",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::Transfer learning}} refers to {{c1::techniques that try to borrow information from other models.}}",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "c*_*qviV+v",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::Semi-supervised learning}} refers to {{c1::techniques for learning from data where only some samples are labeled.}}&nbsp;",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "Q^!#6zo2yc",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::Transductive learning}} refers to {{c1::classifying available unlabeled data based on available labeled data}}",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "j~iO:}]11Y",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::Inductive learning}} refers to {{c1::classifying available <b>and&nbsp;</b>future unlabeled data based on available labeled data}}<br>",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "Jexs3*FKpp",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::Active learning}} systems are called that because they {{c1::actively query the user for additional}} labels.",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "rpa?Qm8Ia1",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::Active learning}} systems use an {{c1::acquisition function}} to determine {{c1::which additional labels would most reduce risk on expectation}}.<br>",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "KU9N3DA/bj",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::Multi-view learning}} refers to {{c1::learning from combinations of different types of data, e.g. image and its caption.}}",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "ps:R8m2Cs~",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::<b>Multi-task learning</b> (MTL)}}&nbsp;refers to {{c1::a type of tranfer learning where multiple learning tasks are solved at the same time}}<br>",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "A1if//h!+f",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::Domain adaptation}} refers to {{c1::a type of transfer learning where a model of a similar but different distribution is transformed to fit a new distribution.}}",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "nnhV%JEX.N",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "In general, machine learning is about optimizing {{c1::the generalization error}}<br>",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "LCA{w:j?da",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::<b>Risk</b>}} is defined as {{c1::the <b>expected loss</b> over the distribution generating the data points}}",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "J6ddb,oi!3",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "There are two major theoretical formulations of risk:<br><br>{{c2::Statistical learning theory}} and {{c1::Bayesian statistics}}",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "E&kU;y8T_}",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "{{c2::Statistical learning theory}}&nbsp;treats the data generation process as {{c1::truly unknown}}, and tries to {{c1::bound the risk}} based on {{c1::estimates computed from available data}}.<br>",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": ":KD2PoG(+",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "As opposed to SLT, {{c2::Bayesian}} statistics assumes {{c1::we know a model but are just unsure of the parameters}}.<br>",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "MO{HE1IzH/",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "Because Bayesian models {{c1::make stronger assumptions about the generating distribution}}, they typically have higher {{c2::bias}} but lower {{c2::variance}}.<br>",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "D_98]G}4AN",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        },
        {
            "__type__": "Note",
            "data": "",
            "fields": [
                "Bayesian decision theory separates modeling into two distinct tasks.<br><br>1. {{c1::Finding the posterior distribution \\( p(\\mathbf \\theta | \\mathcal D ) \\)}}<br>2. {{c1::Making decisions that minimize the risk}}",
                ""
            ],
            "flags": 0,
            "guid": "lb)L#HwTK/",
            "note_model_uuid": "451bea4e-62cb-11ea-a3f6-6fdbf6637bfa",
            "tags": []
        }
    ]
